title: Amazing photos of the Daintree
text:
Amazing photos of the Daintree Christina Pfeiffer | 24th Jul 2015 4:19 PM Christina Pfeiffer The Daintree, Queensland. Photo: David White Popular Stories   
Most people who go to the Daintree want to see crocodiles. Crocodiles are impressive indeed but there are plenty of other natural sights worth a look while visiting north Queensland. 
Here are some amazing photos (love the one of the snake eating a frog!) snapped by photographer David White, whose office is the natural world of Tropical North Queensland. 
Take a peek into David's world and discover the wonders of the Daintree .
